HEADWORD: nuclear fission
<hw>nuclear fission</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A nuclear reaction in which
a heavy atomic nucleus splits into smaller nuclei with the simultaneous
release of energy.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fission.</syn>⟦br⟧
